    {"id": "AS040", "section": "Auto and Shop Information", "topic": "Tools", "question_text": "A torque wrench is used to:", "options": ["Break loose very tight bolts", "Tighten fasteners to a specified torque value (foot-pounds or Newton-meters)", "Measure bolt diameter", "Remove stripped bolts"], "correct_index": 1, "difficulty": 1, "explanation": "A torque wrench tightens fasteners to an exact specification. Critical fasteners (cylinder head bolts, lug nuts, suspension components) have torque specs that ensure proper clamping force without over-tightening and breaking bolts.", "test_types": ["ASVAB"]},
